I mean the tests currently look like this:
return (fieldName, params, lookup) -> (ctx) -> new BooleanFieldScript(fieldName, params, lookup, ctx) {
                                    @Override
                                    public void execute() {
                                        for (Object foo : (List<?>) getSource().get("foo")) {
                                            emit((Boolean) foo);
                                        }
                                    }
                                };

where lookup is passed as a parameter to the lambda, so we could rewrite them like this:
return (fieldName, params, lookup) -> (ctx) -> new BooleanFieldScript(fieldName, params, lookup, ctx) {
                                    @Override
                                    public void execute() {
                                        for (Object foo : (List<?>) lookup.source().get("foo")) {
                                            emit((Boolean) foo);
                                        }
                                    }
                                };
